Note:
==============================================================================
MARKDOWN - CommonMark 0.31 + GFM AST, Parser, and Renderer
==============================================================================

Implements the Markdown abstract syntax tree, a parser covering the most
heavily used block and inline constructs of the CommonMark 0.31
specification (https://spec.commonmark.org/0.31/) plus the strikethrough
and task-list GitHub Flavored Markdown extensions
(https://github.github.com/gfm/), and HTML and plain-text renderers.

AST shapes
----------

MarkdownBlock (tagged 32-byte record):
    slot 0  kind tag         MD_BLOCK_*
    slot 1  primary payload  (NUL-terminated string or List ptr)
    slot 2  secondary        (numeric flag or auxiliary pointer)
    slot 3  inline children  (List of MarkdownInline or 0)

  MD_BLOCK_THEMATIC_BREAK      1
  MD_BLOCK_ATX_HEADING         2   payload = title text, secondary = level
  MD_BLOCK_SETEXT_HEADING      3   payload = title text, secondary = level
  MD_BLOCK_INDENTED_CODE       4   payload = code body
  MD_BLOCK_FENCED_CODE         5   payload = code body, secondary = info str
  MD_BLOCK_HTML_BLOCK          6   payload = raw HTML body
  MD_BLOCK_LINK_REFERENCE_DEF  7   payload = label
  MD_BLOCK_PARAGRAPH           8   payload = raw text (filled by parse_inlines)
  MD_BLOCK_BLANK_LINE          9
  MD_BLOCK_BLOCK_QUOTE        10   payload = List of MarkdownBlocks
  MD_BLOCK_LIST_ITEM          11   payload = List of MarkdownBlocks
  MD_BLOCK_LIST               12   payload = List of MD_BLOCK_LIST_ITEM,
                                   secondary = ordered/loose/start packed
  MD_BLOCK_TABLE_ROW          13   payload = List of cell strings (GFM)
  MD_BLOCK_MATH_BLOCK         14   payload = LaTeX-style display math body

MarkdownInline (tagged 32-byte record, same layout):
  MD_INLINE_TEXT              1   payload = text string
  MD_INLINE_EMPHASIS          2   children = inner inlines, secondary = strength
  MD_INLINE_CODE_SPAN         3   payload = code text
  MD_INLINE_LINK              4   payload = href, secondary = title, children = label
  MD_INLINE_AUTO_LINK         5   payload = href
  MD_INLINE_IMAGE             6   payload = src, secondary = alt text
  MD_INLINE_HARD_LINE_BREAK   7
  MD_INLINE_SOFT_LINE_BREAK   8
  MD_INLINE_HTML_INLINE       9   payload = raw HTML text
  MD_INLINE_MATH_INLINE      10   payload = math body
  MD_INLINE_FOOTNOTE         11   payload = label
  MD_INLINE_STRIKETHROUGH    12   children = inner inlines
  MD_INLINE_TASK             13   secondary = 1 if checked else 0

Parser strategy
---------------

Two passes:

Block pass scans the source line-by-line.  Each line is classified
into one of: blank, ATX heading (CommonMark 4.2), thematic break
(CommonMark 4.1), fenced code opening (CommonMark 4.5), block-quote
marker (CommonMark 5.1), paragraph continuation, or fenced-code
interior.  Open paragraphs and quote bodies accumulate in builders and
emit when terminated.

Inline pass scans every paragraph and heading's payload, emitting
inline records.  Implements: text spans (default), backslash escapes
of ASCII punctuation (CommonMark 2.4), code spans with matching
backtick-runs (CommonMark 6.1), emphasis with simple flanking
(CommonMark 6.2), inline links `[label](href "title")` (CommonMark
6.5), autolinks `<scheme:...>` and `<user@host>` (CommonMark 6.4),
hard line breaks (two-space-at-eol per 6.7), and soft line breaks at
LF.  GFM strikethrough `~~x~~` (GFM 6.5) is also supported.

Lifetimes
---------

Every block and inline node owns its payload strings, info strings,
attribute lists, and child node lists.  markdown_destroy releases the
entire tree.  Strings in payloads must come from Layout.allocate (this
module's parser produces them via StringPrim.string_substring or
similar) so the matching deallocator can free them.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/string_builder.runa" as SB

Note: ============================================================================
Note: BLOCK / INLINE TAG CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Constant MD_BLOCK_THEMATIC_BREAK as Integer is 1
Constant MD_BLOCK_ATX_HEADING as Integer is 2
Constant MD_BLOCK_SETEXT_HEADING as Integer is 3
Constant MD_BLOCK_INDENTED_CODE as Integer is 4
Constant MD_BLOCK_FENCED_CODE as Integer is 5
Constant MD_BLOCK_HTML_BLOCK as Integer is 6
Constant MD_BLOCK_LINK_REFERENCE_DEF as Integer is 7
Constant MD_BLOCK_PARAGRAPH as Integer is 8
Constant MD_BLOCK_BLANK_LINE as Integer is 9
Constant MD_BLOCK_BLOCK_QUOTE as Integer is 10
Constant MD_BLOCK_LIST_ITEM as Integer is 11
Constant MD_BLOCK_LIST as Integer is 12
Constant MD_BLOCK_TABLE_ROW as Integer is 13
Constant MD_BLOCK_MATH_BLOCK as Integer is 14

Constant MD_INLINE_TEXT as Integer is 1
Constant MD_INLINE_EMPHASIS as Integer is 2
Constant MD_INLINE_CODE_SPAN as Integer is 3
Constant MD_INLINE_LINK as Integer is 4
Constant MD_INLINE_AUTO_LINK as Integer is 5
Constant MD_INLINE_IMAGE as Integer is 6
Constant MD_INLINE_HARD_LINE_BREAK as Integer is 7
Constant MD_INLINE_SOFT_LINE_BREAK as Integer is 8
Constant MD_INLINE_HTML_INLINE as Integer is 9
Constant MD_INLINE_MATH_INLINE as Integer is 10
Constant MD_INLINE_FOOTNOTE as Integer is 11
Constant MD_INLINE_STRIKETHROUGH as Integer is 12
Constant MD_INLINE_TASK as Integer is 13

Constant MD_RECORD_SIZE as Integer is 32
Constant MD_OFF_KIND as Integer is 0
Constant MD_OFF_PAYLOAD as Integer is 8
Constant MD_OFF_SECONDARY as Integer is 16
Constant MD_OFF_CHILDREN as Integer is 24

Constant MD_OK as Integer is 0
Constant MD_NULL_ARG as Integer is -1

Constant ASCII_NEWLINE as Integer is 10
Constant ASCII_SPACE as Integer is 32
Constant ASCII_TAB as Integer is 9
Constant ASCII_HASH as Integer is 35
Constant ASCII_GT as Integer is 62
Constant ASCII_LT as Integer is 60
Constant ASCII_DASH as Integer is 45
Constant ASCII_UNDERSCORE as Integer is 95
Constant ASCII_STAR as Integer is 42
Constant ASCII_BACKTICK as Integer is 96
Constant ASCII_BANG as Integer is 33
Constant ASCII_LBRACKET as Integer is 91
Constant ASCII_RBRACKET as Integer is 93
Constant ASCII_LPAREN as Integer is 40
Constant ASCII_RPAREN as Integer is 41
Constant ASCII_QUOTE as Integer is 34
Constant ASCII_BACKSLASH as Integer is 92
Constant ASCII_AMP as Integer is 38
Constant ASCII_TILDE as Integer is 126

Note: ============================================================================
Note: RECORD ALLOCATION HELPERS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a tagged 32-byte record used for both blocks and inlines.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Layout.allocate(32); write the four slots; children slot defaults to 0
so consumers know whether an inline pass has populated it.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on OOM.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "md_record_alloc" takes kind as Integer, payload as Integer, secondary as Integer returns Integer:
    Let rec be proc allocate from Layout with MD_RECORD_SIZE
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, MD_OFF_KIND, kind
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, MD_OFF_PAYLOAD, payload
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, MD_OFF_SECONDARY, secondary
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, MD_OFF_CHILDREN, 0
    Return rec
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PUBLIC BLOCK CONSTRUCTORS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct an ATX heading per CommonMark 4.2.  Level is clamped to 1..6.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
md_record_alloc with MD_BLOCK_ATX_HEADING and clamped level.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Caller transfers ownership of the title string.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "md_atx_heading" takes title as Integer, level as Integer returns Integer:
    Let lvl be level
    If lvl is less than 1:
        Set lvl to 1
    End If
    If lvl is greater than 6:
        Set lvl to 6
    End If
    Return proc md_record_alloc with MD_BLOCK_ATX_HEADING, title, lvl
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct a Setext heading per CommonMark 4.3.  Level is 1 (==) or 2 (--).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
md_record_alloc with MD_BLOCK_SETEXT_HEADING.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Owned title string.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "md_setext_heading" takes title as Integer, level as Integer returns Integer:
    Let lvl be level
    If lvl is less than 1:
        Set lvl to 1
    End If
    If lvl is greater than 2:
        Set lvl to 2
    End If
    Return proc md_record_alloc with MD_BLOCK_SETEXT_HEADING, title, lvl
End Process

